# PortDiary AI (runtime)

**Cursor rules do not change user-facing AI** — they guide dev edits to `ai.js` and context builders.

## 4 features (weekly quota)
| Feature | Route | Response |
|---------|-------|----------|
| Copilot | `POST /ai/copilot` | plain text |
| Analyze | `POST /ai/analyze` | JSON (`parseClaudeJson`) |
| News | `POST /ai/news-summary` | JSON |
| Ticker journal | `POST /ai/ticker-journal` | plain text |

## 2 plans + privileged
- `free` / `pro` in `backend/src/lib/aiPlan.js`
- Owner email (`AI_OWNER_EMAIL`) + `admin` → Pro limits, unlimited quota
- Pro only: `allowCustomQuestion` on Copilot (`COPILOT_CUSTOM_PRO_ONLY`)

## Required in every prompt
- ภาษาไทย
- อ้างอิงเฉพาะข้อมูลใน context — ห้ามแต่ง ticker/ตัวเลข
- ไม่ใช่คำแนะนำซื้อขาย

## Context builders
- `buildAnalyzePayload` / `buildCopilotContext` — use `displayCurrency` + `fxRate` for values
- Plan caps: `maxTransactions`, `maxJournal`, `maxHoldings`, `maxTokens`
- UI presets: `COPILOT_PRESETS` in `aiCopilotContext.js` + mirror in `AIPanel.jsx`

## Do not
- Mix Copilot plain-text prompts with Analyze JSON schema
- Change `weeklyLimit` without updating `subscriptionCatalog.js` labels
- Skip `requireAiQuota` / `reserveAiQuota` on new AI routes
- Edit only system prompt when bug is wrong numbers — fix context first
